This paper deals with recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and their application to language modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes new regularization and optimization techniques for LSTMs, which are machine learning models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of non-monotonic conditions, which is a technique used in optimization algorithms, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of a neural cache, which is a technique used in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
